esqlQuery.esql:
// Alert triggers when errors occur during AWS Bedrock AgentCore Gateway invocations.
//
// Gateway provides a unified API endpoint that enables agents to securely connect
// to enterprise tools and external resources. It acts as a proxy that handles
// authentication, authorization, and routing of requests.
//
// This alert monitors both:
// - User errors (4xx): Client-side errors like invalid requests, unauthorized access
// - System errors (5xx): Server-side errors indicating infrastructure issues
//
// The alert is grouped by cloud account, region, and resource to pinpoint the
// specific gateway experiencing issues.
//
// To reduce alert noise, increase the threshold (e.g., `total_errors > 5`) to only
// alert on sustained error patterns.
// For more details, see: https://docs.aws.amazon.com/bedrock-agentcore/latest/devguide/observability-gateway-metrics.html

FROM metrics-aws_bedrock_agentcore.metrics-*
| WHERE aws.dimensions.Operation == "InvokeGateway"
| STATS total_user_errors = sum(aws.bedrock_agentcore.metrics.UserErrors.sum), total_system_errors = sum(aws.bedrock_agentcore.metrics.SystemErrors.sum) BY cloud.account.id, cloud.region, aws.dimensions.Resource
| EVAL total_errors = COALESCE(total_user_errors, TO_LONG(0)) + COALESCE(total_system_errors, TO_LONG(0))
| WHERE total_errors > 0
